article.headline: Utah Valley St. 81, Texas-Pan American 76
article.story: EDINBURG, Texas (AP) -- David Heck had 23 points and seven rebounds in Utah Valley State's 81-76 victory over Texas-Pan American on Saturday. Heck was 7-of-11 from the field and 5-of-7 from 3-point range. Ryan Toolson came off the bench to add 17 points, while Chris Bailey and Joe Walker each scored 12. The Wolverines (17-7) led 34-32 at the break and built a 10-point lead with 4:43 remaining in the game. They led the Broncs (12-11) in rebounds, points in the paint and points off turnovers. Paul Stoll scored 23 points, including four 3-pointers, to lead Texas-Pan American. Brian Burrell added 17 points and grabbed a team-high nine rebounds. Colin Lien came off the bench to score 16 points, seven from the free throw line.
